version_description: I move the chords around the neck for a more fullness to different parts of the song. (i.e. use bar chords along with open chords).

Mr. Cross recorded this song using Open D. This version uses standard tuning with chords meant to show the movement of the treble part. The chord names say/show exactly which strings are played without resorting to tabbing the whole song. (If you want to give Open D a try, see the Tab version called "Sailing Acoustic".).

Simplified most of the chords as best I could. Omitted the lengthy passages without words. The feel of this song is really tough to grasp without listening to it while you try to play along for a while before trying it solo.
